<% content_for :title, "Privacy Policy — Turf Totals" %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "How Turf Totals collects, uses, and protects your data. Plain-language privacy policy for the skill-based World Cup pick'em game." %>

<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto py-10 px-2 space-y-12">
  <header>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-heading mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-secondary text-sm">Last updated <%= Date.today.strftime("%B %d, %Y") %>.</p>
  </header>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
      This policy explains what information Turf Totals collects, why we collect it, and the
      choices you have. We try to collect as little as possible, and we never sell your
      personal data.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Information we collect</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-body space-y-2">
      <li>
        <strong>Account details.</strong> If you sign in by email we store your email address to
        send you a one-time magic link &mdash; we do not store passwords. If you sign in with a
        Solana wallet (such as Phantom) we store your public wallet address. You may optionally
        set a display name and username, which are public on contest leaderboards.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Sign-in with Google.</strong> If you choose Google sign-in, we receive your email
        address and basic profile information from Google to create or match your account.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Gameplay data.</strong> Your contest entries, picks, scores, and referral activity.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Payment data.</strong> Token and entry-fee purchases are processed by
        <strong>Stripe</strong>. We never see or store your full card number; Stripe handles card
        data under its own PCI-compliant systems. We retain a purchase audit record (amount,
        Stripe session id, status) to fulfill your order and for accounting.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>On-chain data.</strong> Contest entries, prize pools, and payouts settle on the
        public Solana blockchain. Your wallet address and the associated transactions are
        inherently public on-chain &mdash; this is true of any Solana application, not unique to us.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Technical &amp; usage data.</strong> Standard server logs (IP address, browser type,
        pages visited) and approximate location derived from IP for the eligibility check
        described below.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">How we use your information</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-body space-y-2">
      <li>To run the game: create your account, record entries, score contests, and distribute payouts.</li>
      <li>To process token and entry-fee purchases through Stripe.</li>
      <li>To send transactional email (magic-link sign-in, receipts, account notices) via our email provider, Resend.</li>
      <li>To confirm you are accessing the game from a permitted jurisdiction (geo-eligibility).</li>
      <li>To detect and prevent fraud, abuse, and multi-account referral manipulation.</li>
      <li>To diagnose bugs and improve the product.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Analytics and session replay</h2>
    <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
      We use error monitoring (Sentry) and, on a sampled basis, session-replay tooling (LogRocket)
      to reproduce and fix bugs. When session replay is active we identify your session by an
      <strong>opaque account slug only</strong> &mdash; we deliberately do <em>not</em> send your email
      address or other personal identifiers to these vendors. Your public display name may be
      attached because it already appears on leaderboards.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Who we share data with</h2>
    <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
      We share data only with the service providers that make the game work, and only the data
      they need:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-body space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Stripe</strong> &mdash; payment processing.</li>
      <li><strong>Resend</strong> &mdash; transactional email delivery.</li>
      <li><strong>Solana RPC providers</strong> &mdash; reading and broadcasting on-chain transactions.</li>
      <li><strong>Google</strong> &mdash; only if you use Google sign-in.</li>
      <li><strong>Sentry / LogRocket</strong> &mdash; error monitoring and bug reproduction, as described above.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
      We do not sell your personal information. We may disclose information if required by law or
      to protect the rights, safety, and integrity of the game and its players.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Cookies</h2>
    <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
      We use a small number of first-party cookies that are necessary for the site to work &mdash;
      principally your sign-in session and CSRF protection. We do not use third-party advertising
      cookies.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Data retention</h2>
    <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
      We keep account and gameplay data for as long as your account is active. Payment audit
      records are retained as required for accounting and dispute resolution. Operational logs
      are trimmed on a rolling basis. On-chain data is permanent and outside our control by the
      nature of public blockchains.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Your choices and rights</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-body space-y-2">
      <li>You can update your display name and username on your account page at any time.</li>
      <li>You can unlink Google sign-in from your account.</li>
      <li>
        You can request access to, correction of, or deletion of your personal data by emailing
        us. Note we cannot delete data already written to the public Solana blockchain.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Children</h2>
    <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
      Turf Totals is not directed to children. You must be of legal age in your jurisdiction to
      use the game.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading">Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
      We may update this policy as the product evolves. Material changes will be reflected by the
      &ldquo;last updated&rdquo; date above.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-2 text-sm text-secondary border-t border-subtle pt-6">
    <p>
      Questions about your privacy? Email
      <a href="mailto:alex@turfmonster.media" class="text-primary hover:underline">alex@turfmonster.media</a>.
      See also our
      <%= link_to "Terms of Service", terms_path, class: "text-primary hover:underline" %>
      and
      <%= link_to "About page", about_path, class: "text-primary hover:underline" %>.
    </p>
  </section>
</div>
